<p>This feature creates window of <strong>Access Terms</strong> to allow or deny userâ€™s access to webpage. Unless the admin approves it, access to website is denied and the user will be redirected outside of the website.</p>

<p>To activate this feature go to <strong>Admin Panel</strong>, and create new page. By clicking on <strong>Content</strong> &gt; <strong>Page</strong> option, then a blue button <strong>New</strong>. If you are not sure on how to create new page, check <a href="//docs.yclas.com/how_to_add_pages">here</a>!</p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/access-terms.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/access-terms.png" alt="Activate Access Term Alert" />
</a></p>

<p>After you created new page, go to <strong>Settings &gt; General</strong>, and find the option <strong>Accept Terms Alert</strong>. Then in one of the following options should be your new page. Select it, and click on <strong>Save</strong> button.</p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/access-terms2.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/access-terms2.png" alt="Activate Access Term Alert" />
</a></p>

<p>Thatâ€™s it, you activated the <strong>Access Terms Alert</strong>. Now refresh your home page, and it should pop a window like this:</p>

<p>Once itâ€™s accepted, terms wont appear again unless you <strong>clean your cookies</strong>.</p>

